'''Alfred Victor Espinas''' (23 May 1844 – 24 February 1922) was a French thinker noted for having been an influence on [[Nietzsche]]. He was a [[student]] of [[Auguste Comte|Comte]] and [[Herbert Spencer|Spencer]]. Although initially an adherent of [[positivism]], he later became a committed [[realism (philosophy)|realist]].
He died in [[Saint-Florentin, Yonne]].
== Works == * ''Des sociétés animales'' (1877) * ''Les origines de la technologie'' (1897) * ''La philosophie sociale du XVIIIe siècle et la Révolution'' (1898) * ''Descartes et la morale: Études sur l'histoire de la philosophie de l'action'' (1925)
==References== *Jean Ostrowski, ''Alfred Espinas, précurseur de la praxéologie: Ses antécédents et ses successeurs'', Librairie Générale de Droit et de Jurisprudence, Paris, 1973
