{{Infobox philosopher |region = [[Western philosophy]] |era = [[Contemporary philosophy|21st-century philosophy]] |color = |image = |name = '''Gregory Fernando Pappas''' |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1960|2|9}} |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |school_tradition = [[Pragmatism]] | institutions = [[Texas A&M University]] |main_interests = [[Inter-American philosophy]] | thesis_title = | thesis_url = | thesis_year = | doctoral_advisor = | doctoral_students = |notable_ideas = | spouse = | education = | alma_mater = [[University of Texas at Austin]] (Ph.D.) |influences = [[John Dewey]], [[William James]], [[Luis Villoro]] |influenced = |awards = [[Ford Foundation Postdoctoral Fellowship]], the William James and the Latin American Thought prizes, Mellow Prize |website = http://goyopappas.com/ }}
''' Gregory “Goyo” Fernando Pappas''' (born February 9, 1960) is an American philosopher and Professor of Philosophy at [[Texas A&M University]]. He is also Distinguished Research Fellow for the Latino Research Initiative at [[The University of Texas at Austin]]. Pappas is the editor-in-chief of ''[[The Inter-American Journal of Philosophy]]''.<ref>{{cite web |title=John Dewey’s Ethics: Democracy as Experience, by Gregory Fernando Pappas |url=https://philosophy.tamu.edu/john-deweys-ethics-democracy-as-experience-by-gregory-fernando-pappas/ |website=philosophy.tamu.edu |accessdate=1 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=LRI Distinguished Lecture: Gregory Fernando Pappas |url=https://calendar.utexas.edu/event/lri_distinguished_lecture_gregory_fernando_pappas |website=UT Events Calendar |accessdate=1 August 2018 |language=en}}</ref>
==Books== * ''John Dewey’s Ethics: Democracy as Experience'' * ''Pragmatism in the Americas''
